clearcontrol.core.concurrent.executors

Interface AsynchronousExecutorFeature

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AdaptationModuleInterface<S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AdaptationModuleBase, AdaptationTestModule, AdaptiveEngine, AsynchronousProcessor, AsynchronousProcessorBase, AsynchronousProcessorNull, AsynchronousProcessorPool, AsynchronousProcessorToString, GS16AO64cScoreCompiler, GS16AO64cSignalGenerator, HamStackCamera, LabelGridDemo, LoopTaskDevice, MicroscopeGUI, NDIteratorAdaptationModule, NIRIOScoreCompiler, NIRIOSignalGenerator, ObjectVariableAsynchronousProcessorPool, PeriodicLoopTaskDevice, RecyclerPaneDemo, ScriptingEngine, SignalGeneratorBase, SignalGeneratorSimulatorDevice, StackCameraDeviceSimulator, StackRecyclerManagerPanelDemo, TaskDevice, TC01, TemperatureSensorDeviceBase, TemperatureSensorDeviceSimulator, TimelapseBase, VariableLCDDemo, VariableSliderDemo

    public interface AsynchronousExecutorFeature
    This interface provides classes that implement it the basic infrastructure to execute Runnables and Callables asynchronously from the calling thread. Each instance of this class is provided with an Executor (configurable) that is automatically allocated. You simply have to call the method 'executeAsynchronously' such as for example: executAsynchronously(() -> {System.out.println("tada...")}) And this code will be executed in a separate thread. The executAsynchronously(0 method returns a Future that can be used to determine when is the task finished.
    Author:
    royer
